companyProfile.companyDescription: UltraTech Cement Limited is an India-based company, which is engaged in the business of manufacturing and sale of cement and cement related products. The Company’s products include UltraTech Cement, Ready Mix Concrete, Building Solutions, Building Products. Its UltraTech Cement products include Ordinary Portland Cement (OPC), Portland Pozzolana Cement (PPC), and Portland Slag Cement (PSC). Its Building Solutions products include cement, steels, painting system, waterproofing and chemicals, electricals, plywood, shuttering ply, power and hand tools, flooring, pipes, sanitary ware, mortars, roofing, and water storage tanks. Its Building Products includes Tiles Adhesives (TILEFIXO-CT, TILEFIXO-VT, TILEFIXO-NT, and TILEFIXO-YT), Repair Products (MICROKRETE and BASEKRETE), Waterproofing Products(SEAL & DRY, FLEX, HIFLEX, and MYKROFILL), Industrial and Precision Grout (POWERGROUT NS1, NS2, and NS3), Masonry Products (FIXOBLOCK), and Light Weight Autoclaved Aerated Concrete Block (XTRALITE).

recentNews.headline: Stock Market Strategy: InCred Equities lists 21 stocks to buy this June
recentNews.intro: Despite a 4% gain in benchmark indices in 2025, Indian equity markets remain volatile due to global trade tensions. InCred Equities recommends 21 stocks with an ?Add? rating, highlighting a favorable monsoon and strong GVA growth as key positives for investors.
recentNews.imagecaption: Stock Market Strategy: InCred Equities lists 21 stocks to buy this June

recentNews.headline: Stocks to buy: Cement sector set for steady growth in FY26; brokerages bullish on THESE four stocks
recentNews.intro: Cement stocks are poised for growth as the sector rebounded in Q4FY25, with top firms achieving strong results and capacity expansions. Analysts predict demand growth between 6-9% in FY26, driven by urbanization and infrastructure investments, despite potential seasonal challenges.
recentNews.imagecaption: Stocks to buy: Cement sector set for steady growth in FY26; brokerages prefer UltraTech, JK Cement, and Ambuja Cements

recentNews.headline: Polycab shone in FY25, but will investors stay plugged in?
recentNews.intro: A stellar Q4FY25 helped the company surpass its  ?20,000-crore revenue goal in FY25, a year ahead of schedule. But it faces increased competition in the domestic wires and cables market with the entrance of UltraTech Cement Ltd and Adani Group.
recentNews.imagecaption: The wires & cables segment contributed 84% of Polycab?s FY25 gross revenues. Image: Pexel

recentNews.headline: Q4 earnings live tracker, 26 May: The latest on how India Inc?s biggest companies fared
recentNews.intro: Watch this page as we bring to you the latest from the ongoing Q4 earnings season, with numbers, charts, and management commentary from India?s biggest listed companies. NTPC, JSW Steel, and Glenmark Pharmaceuticals are among the names that have released their earnings recently.
recentNews.imagecaption: The combined revenue of companies that have reported their March-quarter earnings so far rose 1.8% year-on-year, while aggregate net profit grew over 8%, a Mint analysis showed. (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: UltraTech Cement set for higher volumes, tighter grip on costs
recentNews.intro: Acquisitions would certainly help UltraTech up its market share game, but a lingering concern has been the profitability drag from the sub-optimal acquired assets.
recentNews.imagecaption: UltraTech saw some demand weakness when FY26 began  Photo: REUTERS/Amit Dave.

recentNews.headline: India Cements shares extend post-Q4 results 2025 rally. Jumps 5% in two days
recentNews.intro: India Cements share price increased by 5% after announcing a Q4 profit of  ?14.68 crore for 2025, compared to a loss of  ?60.55 crore the previous year. Revenue declined by 3.11% to  ?1,197.30 crore, while net loss for FY25 reduced to  ?143.88 crore.
recentNews.imagecaption: India Cements shares extend post-Q4 results 2025 rally. Jumps 5% in two days

recentNews.headline: UltraTech Cement share price falls nearly 2% despite 10% rise in Q4 PAT. Should you buy, sell or hold?
recentNews.intro: UltraTech Cement share price dropped nearly 2% despite a 10% YoY rise in net profit to  ?2,482.04 crore. The stock opened at  ?12,200.05, with analysts noting strong support at  ?11,600 and potential upside towards  ?12,800 if momentum continues.
recentNews.imagecaption: UltraTech Cement share price falls nearly 2% despite 10% rise in Q4 PAT. Should you buy, sell or hold?

recentNews.headline: UltraTech Cement Q4 results: PAT rises 10% YoY to  ?2,482 crore; declares  ?77.50 dividend
recentNews.intro: UltraTech Cement Q4 results: UltraTech Cement reported a 10% YoY rise in consolidated net profit to  ?2,482.04 crore for Q4, with revenue up 13% to  ?23,063.32 crore. The company also achieved over 1GW of renewable power and proposed a 775% dividend.
